    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-06T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-06T05:00:00-05:00" n="438"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d438">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/5–654:Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-06T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 6, 1954—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 111. Repeated information Saigon 35,
                    Paris 204, London 124. Reference Saigon telegram 2202 repeated Geneva 44, Paris
                        752.<note n="1" xml:id="d438fn1">Not printed. (751G.00/5–454)</note> I
                    concur with Saigon that the Secretary might at his next press conference, in
                    reply to a question regarding possible partition of Vietnam, say that the United
                    States advocates a solution firmly based upon the independence, unity and the
                    territorial and political integrity of Vietnam.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
